In [13]:
def extract_ner_entities(text):
    try:
        entities = ner_pipeline(text[:512])  # truncate to fit model input
        orgs = [ent['word'] for ent in entities if ent['entity_group'] == 'ORG']
        people = [ent['word'] for ent in entities if ent['entity_group'] == 'PER']
        locations = [ent['word'] for ent in entities if ent['entity_group'] == 'LOC']
        return orgs, people, locations
    except:
        return [], [], []

import re

def clean_entity(entity):
    entity = entity.strip().title()  # Remove spaces, proper casing
    if len(entity) <= 2:
        return None
    if entity.lower() in {
        'Ai', 'A', 'Us', 'News', 'Rss', 'Etfs', 'Covid'
    }:
        return None
    if not re.search('[a-zA-Z]', entity):
        return None
    if len(entity.split()) > 4:  # overly long phrases
        return None
    return entity

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

def plot_top_entities(counter_data, title, color):
    entities, counts = zip(*counter_data)
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=list(counts), y=list(entities), color=color)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel("Mentions")
    plt.ylabel("Entity")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()



plot_top_entities(top_orgs, "Top 20 Organizations in AI News", color="blue")
plot_top_entities(top_people, "Top 20 People in AI News", color="gold")
plot_top_entities(top_locations, "Top 20 Locations in AI News", color="pink")

# Group by org and industry
org_industry_counts = exploded_df.groupby(['Organizations', 'final_industry']).size().reset_index(name='Mentions')

# Select top 10 orgs by total mentions
top_orgs = pivot_table.sum(axis=1).sort_values(ascending=False).head(10).index
pivot_top_orgs = pivot_table.loc[top_orgs]

# Explode to one row per location

# Optional: filter short / noisy location strings
df_loc = df_loc[df_loc['Locations'].apply(lambda x: len(x) > 2)]

# Group
loc_industry = df_loc.groupby(['Locations', 'final_industry']).size().reset_index(name='Mentions')

# Pivot for heatmap
pivot = loc_industry.pivot(index='Locations', columns='final_industry', values='Mentions').fillna(0)

# Select top 10 locations

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Explode people list to one per row
df_people = sample_df.explode('People')
df_people = df_people[df_people['People'].notnull()]
df_people = df_people[df_people['People'].apply(lambda x: len(x.strip()) > 2)]

# Group by person and industry
people_industry = df_people.groupby(['People', 'final_industry']).size().reset_index(name='Mentions')

# Pivot to matrix
pivot_people = people_industry.pivot(index='People', columns='final_industry', values='Mentions').fillna(0)

# Select top 10 people by total mentions
top_people = pivot_people.sum(axis=1).sort_values(ascending=False).head(9).index
pivot_top_people = pivot_people.loc[top_people]

# Plot heatmap
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.heatmap(pivot_top_people, annot=True, fmt=".0f", cmap="Purples", linewidths=0.5)
plt.title("Top 10 People Mentions by Industry")
plt.ylabel("Person")
plt.xlabel("Industry")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
